"><a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Template:Globalization_sidebar&amp;action=edit"><abbr title="Edit this template">e</abbr></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n<p><b>Economic globalization</b> is one of the three main dimensions of globalization commonly found in academic literature, with the two other being <a href="/wiki/Political_globalization" title="Political globalization">political globalization</a> and <a href="/wiki/Cultural_globalization" title="Cultural globalization">cultural globalization</a>, as well as the general term of <a href="/wiki/Globalization" title="Globalization">globalization</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-Ritzer2008-146_1-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Ritzer2008-146-1">[1]</a></sup></p>\n<table class="vertical-navbox nowraplinks" style="float:right;clear:right;width:22.0em;margin:0 0 1.0em 1.0em;background:#f9f9f9;border:1px solid #aaa;padding:0.2em;border-spacing:0.4em 0;text-align:center;line-height:1.4em;font-size:88%">\n<tr>\n<td style="padding-top:0.4em;line-height:1.2em;padding-bottom:0.2em;">Part of <a href="/wiki/Category:Politics" title="Category:Politics">the Politics series</a> on</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th style="padding:0.2em 0.4em 0.2em;padding-top:0;font-size:145%;line-height:1.2em;font-size:200%;line-height:1.1em;font-weight:normal;"><a href="/wiki/Economic_liberalism" title="Economic liberalism">Economic<br />\nliberalism</a></th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="padding:0.2em 0 0.4em"><a href="/wiki/File:EffectOfTariff.svg" class="image" title="Effect of tariff"><img alt="Effect of tariff" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4d/EffectOfTariff.svg/175px-EffectOfTariff.svg.png" width="175" height="181" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4d/EffectOfTariff.svg/263px-EffectOfTariff.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4d/EffectOfTariff.svg/350px-EffectOfTariff.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="600" data-file-height="620" /></a><